  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which books are preferred by 12 board topper?",
  "response": "High school students aiming for top marks in their 12th board exams often rely on a variety of resources, including textbooks, reference books, and competitive exam preparation books. Some commonly preferred books include:\n\n1. **NCERT Textbooks**: These are indispensable for a thorough understanding of concepts and are often recommended by teachers and toppers alike.\n\n2. **Reference Books**:\n   - Physics: \"Concepts of Physics\" by H.C. Verma, \"Fundamentals of Physics\" by Halliday, Resnick and Walker\n   - Chemistry: \"Organic Chemistry\" by Morrison & Boyd, \"Physical Chemistry\" by P. Bahadur\n   - Mathematics: \"IIT Mathematics\" by M.L. Khanna, \"Problems in Calculus of One Variable\" by I.A. Maron\n   - Biology: \"Biology\" by Campbell & Reece, \"Trueman's Elementary Biology\"\n\n3. **Practice Papers and Guides**:\n   - Arihant Compilations\n   - R.D. Sharma for Mathematics\n   - MTG Interactive Workbooks for various subjects\n   - Oswaal Books Chapter-wise Solutions \n\n4. **Competitive Exam Preparation Books**:\n   - For NEET: \"Objective NCERT at your Fingertips\" by MTG, \"NEET Guide\" by Disha\n   - For JEE: \"Advanced Problems in Organic Chemistry\" by MS Chouhan, \"Cengage Series for JEE\"\n\n5. **Online Resources and Test Series** can also be immensely helpful, such as those provided by platforms like BYJU'S, Vedantu, and Unacademy.\n\nUltimately, the choice of books can vary depending on the stream (Science, Commerce, or Arts) and individual preferences. However, NCERT textbooks are a unanimous choice among toppers for clear concepts and adherence to the board's curriculum.",
